<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3736.5.3>
    bibo:endPage "485" ;
    bibo:issue "5" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "471" ;
    bibo:volume "3736" ;
    dc:creator "Kånneby, Tobias; Jondelius, Ulf" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Four new species of Acoela from Chile" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215892>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215891>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215893> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215892>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2 – 3. 2. Isodiametra finkei n. sp. Photomicrograph of sagittal histological section stained with hematoxylineosin. Scale bar: 100 µm. 3. Isodiametra finkei n. sp. Schematic drawing of dorsal side of specimen. Scale bar: 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/215892/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215891>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Isodiametra finkei n. sp. Photomicrographs of living specimens A – C. A. Dorsal view of whole specimen. Scale bar: 100 µm. B and C. Internal anatomy of posterior end showing the male and female copulatory organs. Note the thick anterior walls of the seminal bursa (arrow). Scale bars: 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/215891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.215893>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Isodiametra finkei n. sp. Details of the 50 % consensus tree after bootstrap analysis of the concatenated 18 S, 28 S and COI dataset showing the position of this species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/215893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

